---
layout: layout-base.njk
layoutClass: "cropCityPage"
pagination:
  data: maturitySummaries
  size: 1
  alias: pageData
permalink: "{{ pageData.url }}index.html"
eleventyComputed:
  title: "Will {{ pageData.cropName }} Mature Before Frost in {{ pageData.cityName }}?"
  description: "See whether {{ pageData.cropName | lower }} usually has enough time and heat to mature before fall frost in {{ pageData.cityName }}, {{ pageData.regionName }}."
  canonical: "https://growbydate.com{{ pageData.url }}"
---

{% set sections = pageData.copy.sections or {} %}
{% set diagnostics = pageData.copy.diagnostics or pageData.diagnostics or {} %}
{% set varietyStrategy = pageData.copy.varietyStrategy or diagnostics.varietyStrategy or {} %}
{% set seasonMath = sections.verdictAndSeasonMath %}
{% set controllingFactor = sections.controllingFactor %}
{% set bufferLoss = sections.bufferLoss %}
{% set successPattern = sections.successPattern %}
{% set recommendedAdjustments = sections.recommendedAdjustments %}

<header class="header">
  <p class="eyebrow">Local maturity outlook for {{ pageData.cityName }}, {{ pageData.regionName }}</p>
  <h1>Will {{ pageData.cropName }} Mature Before Frost in {{ pageData.cityName }}?</h1>

  {% if pageData.copy.fitSummary %}
    <p class="lede">{{ pageData.copy.fitSummary }}</p>
  {% elif seasonMath and seasonMath.intro %}
    <p class="lede">{{ seasonMath.intro }}</p>
  {% endif %}
</header>

<section class="card">
  <div class="quickAnswerTop">
    <h2>Quick answer</h2>

    {% if pageData.copy.maturityFitBadgeLabel %}
      <div class="fitBadge fitBadge-{{ pageData.copy.maturityFitBadgeClass }}">
        {{ pageData.copy.maturityFitBadgeLabel }}
      </div>
    {% endif %}
  </div>

  {% if pageData.copy.maturityFitBoxText %}
    <p style="margin-top:0.85rem;">{{ pageData.copy.maturityFitBoxText }}</p>
  {% endif %}

  {% if pageData.copy.timingSummary %}
    <p>{{ pageData.copy.timingSummary }}</p>
  {% endif %}

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Typical planting date:</strong> {{ pageData.copy.primaryPlantingDateLong or '—' }}</li>
    <li><strong>Typical fall frost:</strong> {{ pageData.copy.fallFrostLong or '—' }}</li>
    <li><strong>Available GDD from the normal planting date:</strong> {{ pageData.heat.availableFromPlanting if pageData.heat.availableFromPlanting != null else '—' }}</li>
    <li><strong>Typical GDD target:</strong> {{ pageData.heat.targetTypical if pageData.heat.targetTypical != null else '—' }}</li>
    <li><strong>Estimated heat margin:</strong> {{ pageData.heat.margin if pageData.heat.margin != null else '—' }}</li>
  </ul>

  {% if pageData.copy.marginMeaning %}
    <p>{{ pageData.copy.marginMeaning }}</p>
  {% elif seasonMath and seasonMath.takeaway %}
    <p>{{ seasonMath.takeaway }}</p>
  {% endif %}
</section>

<section class="card">
  <h2>Why this crop fits here when it works</h2>

  {% if controllingFactor and controllingFactor.intro %}
    <p>{{ controllingFactor.intro }}</p>
  {% elif pageData.copy.priorityLeversIntro %}
    <p>{{ pageData.copy.priorityLeversIntro }}</p>
  {% endif %}

  {% if controllingFactor and controllingFactor.bullets and controllingFactor.bullets.length %}
    <ul>
      {% for item in controllingFactor.bullets %}
        <li>
          <strong>{{ item.label }}:</strong> {{ item.text }}
        </li>
      {% endfor %}
    </ul>
  {% elif pageData.copy.priorityLevers and pageData.copy.priorityLevers.length %}
    <ul>
      {% for item in pageData.copy.priorityLevers %}
        <li>
          <strong>{{ item.title }}:</strong> {{ item.text }}
        </li>
      {% endfor %}
    </ul>
  {% endif %}

  {% if pageData.copy.whatBreaksFirst and pageData.copy.fitRank <= 2 %}
    <p>{{ pageData.copy.whatBreaksFirst }}</p>
  {% endif %}

  {% if pageData.copy.timeVsHeatDiagnosis %}
    <p>{{ pageData.copy.timeVsHeatDiagnosis }}</p>
  {% endif %}

  {% if successPattern and successPattern.intro %}
    <p>{{ successPattern.intro }}</p>
  {% elif pageData.copy.realisticSuccessCase %}
    <p>{{ pageData.copy.realisticSuccessCase }}</p>
  {% else %}
    <p>
      The best way to read this climate fit is not as a yes-or-no promise, but as a pattern. Some crops
      usually finish comfortably from the normal schedule. Others can mature here, but only if the grower
      protects the early season, avoids wasted time, and stays realistic about variety speed.
    </p>
  {% endif %}

  <p>
    In other words, the local maturity outlook is not just about whether {{ pageData.copy.cropConceptPhrase }}
    can finish before frost in a perfect season. It is about whether the crop still looks sensible once you account
    for the way real seasons and real gardens behave.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <h2>What usually erodes the margin</h2>

  {% if bufferLoss and bufferLoss.intro %}
    <p>{{ bufferLoss.intro }}</p>
  {% elif pageData.timing and pageData.timing.delayAnalysis and pageData.timing.delayAnalysis.summary %}
    <p>{{ pageData.timing.delayAnalysis.summary }}</p>
  {% else %}
    <p>
      Even when the season math looks comfortable, the working margin still gets smaller once planting slips,
      early growth slows, or the crop spends part of the season recovering instead of advancing.
    </p>
  {% endif %}

  {% if bufferLoss and bufferLoss.bullets and bufferLoss.bullets.length %}
    <ul>
      {% for item in bufferLoss.bullets %}
        <li>
          <strong>{{ item.label }}:</strong> {{ item.text }}
        </li>
      {% endfor %}
    </ul>
  {% elif pageData.timing and pageData.timing.delayAnalysis and pageData.timing.delayAnalysis.rows and pageData.timing.delayAnalysis.rows.length %}
    <ul>
      {% for item in pageData.timing.delayAnalysis.rows %}
        <li>
          <strong>{{ item.label }}:</strong>
          {% if item.date %}
            {{ item.date | mmddLong }}
          {% else %}
            —
          {% endif %}
          {% if item.gddMargin != null %}
            — about {{ item.gddMargin }} GDD of margin
          {% endif %}
        </li>
      {% endfor %}
    </ul>
  {% endif %}

  {% if diagnostics.decisionProfile == "very_comfortable" %}
    <p>
      This is mostly a flexibility question. Very comfortable local fits usually absorb ordinary delays, but the table shows how much margin you are still spending when timing slips.
    </p>
  {% elif diagnostics.decisionProfile == "comfortable" %}
    <p>
      This is mostly a flexibility question. Comfortable local fits usually absorb ordinary delays, but the table shows how much margin you are still spending when timing slips.
    </p>
  {% elif diagnostics.decisionProfile == "workable" %}
    <p>
      This is the practical difference between a crop that is workable and one that feels easy. A decent fit can still narrow faster than it first appears once timing slips.
    </p>
  {% elif diagnostics.decisionProfile == "tight" %}
    <p>
      This is where a narrow fit becomes more fragile. Even modest delay can erase much of the usable margin and push the crop toward a more conditional finish.
    </p>
  {% endif %}
</section>

{% if pageData.fit.varietyClassFits and pageData.fit.varietyClassFits.length %}
<section class="card">
  <h2>Which variety speeds fit best</h2>

  <p>
    Variety choice matters because “can this crop mature here?” is rarely one single answer.
    Faster classes protect margin. Slower classes spend it. That changes not just whether the crop can finish,
    but how much room is left for ordinary delays and uneven early growth.
  </p>

  {% if varietyStrategy.defaultRecommendedVarietyLabel %}
    <p>
      The default recommendation here is usually <strong>{{ varietyStrategy.defaultRecommendedVarietyLabel }}</strong>.
      {% if varietyStrategy.fastestReliableVarietyLabel and varietyStrategy.fastestReliableVarietyLabel != varietyStrategy.defaultRecommendedVarietyLabel %}
        If you want the safest end of the range, start with <strong>{{ varietyStrategy.fastestReliableVarietyLabel }}</strong>.
      {% endif %}
      {% if varietyStrategy.slowestStillFittingVarietyLabel and varietyStrategy.slowestStillFittingVarietyLabel != varietyStrategy.defaultRecommendedVarietyLabel %}
        The slowest class that still looks locally workable is <strong>{{ varietyStrategy.slowestStillFittingVarietyLabel }}</strong>.
      {% endif %}
    </p>
  {% endif %}

  <ul>
    {% for variety in pageData.fit.varietyClassFits %}
      <li>
        <strong>{{ variety.label }}:</strong>
        {% if variety.margin != null %}
          {{ variety.margin }} GDD margin
          {% if variety.fits %}
            — locally workable from the normal schedule
          {% else %}
            — more of a stretch from the normal schedule
          {% endif %}
        {% else %}
          no local margin estimate
        {% endif %}
      </li>
    {% endfor %}
  </ul>

  <p>
    The useful question here is not just which class technically fits. It is which class leaves enough room
    for the kind of season you actually expect to garden through.
  </p>
</section>
{% endif %}

<section class="card">
  <h2>How to improve your odds</h2>

  {% if recommendedAdjustments and recommendedAdjustments.intro %}
    <p>{{ recommendedAdjustments.intro }}</p>
  {% else %}
    <p>
      The most useful adjustments here are the ones that protect margin early rather than trying to recover it later.
    </p>
  {% endif %}

  {% if pageData.copy.priorityLevers and pageData.copy.priorityLevers.length %}
    <ul>
      {% for item in pageData.copy.priorityLevers %}
        <li>
          <strong>{{ item.title }}:</strong> {{ item.text }}
        </li>
      {% endfor %}
    </ul>
  {% elif recommendedAdjustments and recommendedAdjustments.bullets and recommendedAdjustments.bullets.length %}
    <ul>
      {% for item in recommendedAdjustments.bullets %}
        <li>
          <strong>{{ item.label }}:</strong> {{ item.text }}
        </li>
      {% endfor %}
    </ul>
  {% else %}
    <ul>
      {% if varietyStrategy.defaultRecommendedVarietyLabel %}
        <li>
          <strong>Choose the right maturity range:</strong>
          {{ varietyStrategy.defaultRecommendedVarietyLabel }} is the best default class when you want a realistic local fit.
        </li>
      {% endif %}

      <li>
        <strong>Stay close to the normal schedule:</strong>
        Preserving margin early usually matters more than trying to rescue the crop late.
      </li>

      {% if pageData.strategy.shortSeasonStrategy %}
        <li>
          <strong>Protect the main weakness:</strong>
          {{ pageData.strategy.shortSeasonStrategy }}
        </li>
      {% endif %}
    </ul>
  {% endif %}

  {% if pageData.copy.actionLayer and pageData.copy.actionLayer.length %}
    <p>Good next steps usually look like this:</p>
    <ul>
      {% for item in pageData.copy.actionLayer %}
        <li>{{ item }}</li>
      {% endfor %}
    </ul>
  {% endif %}
</section>

<section class="card">
  <h2>Related planning pages for {{ pageData.cropName }} in {{ pageData.cityName }}</h2>

  <p>
    Use these pages when you want to move from the broad maturity question into timing, late planting, or variety choice.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <a href="{{ pageData.urlBase }}">Main {{ pageData.copy.cropNameLower }} planting guide for {{ pageData.cityName }}</a>
      — use this for the normal planting window and the overall local crop plan.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="{{ pageData.urlBase }}is-it-too-late-to-plant/">Is it too late to plant {{ pageData.copy.cropNameLower }}?</a>
      — use this when you are already behind the normal schedule and want to know whether the answer has changed.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="{{ pageData.urlBase }}best-varieties/">Best {{ pageData.copy.cropNameLower }} varieties for {{ pageData.cityName }}</a>
      — use this when the crop itself looks possible, but maturity class is what will decide how safe or ambitious the plan is.
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>

{% include "planting-dates/modules/faq-block.njk" %}